{"lemma":"صَوابٌ","slug":"صَوابٌ","root":"ص.#.ب","root_slug":"ص-_-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ص-_-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"صَواب","root":"صوب","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n23590","n23591","n25121"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B5%D9%8E%D9%88%D8%A7%D8%A8%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"correctness, right"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"accuracy, rightness, truth","examples":[{"text":"سَلُوا قَلْبِي غَدَاةَ سَلَا وَثَابَا\n لَعَلَّ عَلَى ٱلْجَمَالِ لَهُ عِتَابًا\n وَيُسْأَلُ فِي ٱلْحَوَادِثِ ذُو صَوَابٍ\n فَهَلْ تَرَكَ ٱلْجَمَالُ لَهُ صَوَابًا","english":"Ask my heart the early morning it forgets and returns to its previous state\n Perhaps towards the beautiful one it has some reproach\n Only wise people are supposed to be asked\n Did the beauty leave any wisdom to it"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"reason, consciousness, sanity"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"right, correct"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"just"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the root ص و ب (ṣ w b), see also صَوَّبَ (ṣawwaba)."},"ipa":["/sˤa.waːb/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n23590","headword_ar":"صُوَابٌ","root":"SA^b","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see the next paragraph, in three places."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n23591","headword_ar":"صُوَابٌ","root":"SA^b","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) vulgarly pronounced"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuwaAbap","text_ar":"صُوَابَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", without., (MF, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A nit;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an egg of a louse;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an egg of a flea;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) but accord. to some, not applied to the latter unless tropically: (MF, TA:) accord. to IDrst,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a young louse:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"eggs of the flea"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the louse;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Suw^aAbN","text_ar":"صُوَابٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M:) [or,] accord. to the S and K, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Suw^aAbN","text_ar":"صُوَابٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Siy^obaAnN","text_ar":"صِيْبَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) the latter of which is vulgarly pronounced"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SiybaAn","text_ar":"صِيبَان"},{"kind":"text","text":", without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"'","text_ar":"ء"},{"kind":"text","text":", (MF, TA,) are pls. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Suw^aAbapN","text_ar":"صُوَابَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but the former of them is a coll. gen. n., of which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Suw^aAbapN","text_ar":"صُوَابَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the n. un.: (TA:) Yaakoob has erroneously asserted that one should not say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Siy^obaAnN","text_ar":"صِيْبَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, TA.) ―         -b2-  ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Suw^aAbN","text_ar":"صُوَابٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also sometimes applied to (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"small pieces of gold that are taken forth from the dust,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"earth, of the mine."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IDrst, TA.) In the following verse, cited by IAar,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"Hay~aA ↓ \n      yaA rab~i A^awojidoniY Suw^aAbFA\n                      \n                     \n                        famaA A^araY AlT~ay~aAra yugoniY $ay~aA"},{"kind":"text","text":"the poet means, ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O my Lord,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cause me to find gold like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Suw^aAb","text_ar":"صُوَاب"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nits"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whole,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sound, not broken into minute parts;"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for I see not the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tay~aAr","text_ar":"طَيَّار"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to stand in any stead;"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ay~aA","text_ar":"شَيَّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"being for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ayoy^FA","text_ar":"شَيْيًا"},{"kind":"text","text":";] by the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ty~Ar","text_ar":"طيّار"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"minutest pieces of gold that the wind blows away."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, L, TA.) ―         -b3-  And [the pl.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Siy^obaAnN","text_ar":"صِيْبَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies [also] (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Hoar-frost formed into grains like small pearls."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A'Obeyd, L, TA.) [And drops of fine rain are said to be likened to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Siy^obaAn","text_ar":"صِيْبَان"},{"kind":"text","text":": see Ham p. 796. See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SabiY~N","text_ar":"صَبِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sbw","text_ar":"صبو"},{"kind":"text","text":"), last sentence.]"}],"source_refs":["S","K","MF","TA","M"]},{"entry_id":"n25121","headword_ar":"صَوَابٌ","root":"Swb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thing that is right,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or what is said and of what is done; [like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sadaAdN","text_ar":"سَدَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":";] (Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaTaA^N","text_ar":"خَطَاٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, M, Msb, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SawobN","text_ar":"صَوْبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, Msb, K.) One says, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daEoniY waEalaY~a xaTay^iY waSawobiY","text_ar":"دَعْنِى وَعَلَىَّ خَطَيِى وَصَوْبِى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SawaAbiY","text_ar":"صَوَابِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Leave thou me, and on me be"},{"kind":"text","text":"the consequence of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"my wrong saying"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deed, and my right"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) [And hence the phrase, frequent in some of the lexicons &c.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~awaAbu ka*aA","text_ar":"الصَّوَابُ كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The right,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"correct, word"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wording"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reading is thus:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SawaAbuhu ka*aA","text_ar":"صَوَابُهُ كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The right,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"correct, writing"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wording"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reading of it is thus."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b2-  And one says also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qawolN SawobN","text_ar":"قَوْلٌ صَوْبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SawaAbN","text_ar":"صَوَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A right,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"correct, saying:"},{"kind":"text","text":"thus using each as an epithet]. (M.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D8%B5%D9%88%D8%A7%D8%A8/","headword_ar":"صواب","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_18","lexicon_en":"Al-Sharīf al-Jurjānī, Kitāb al-Taʿrīfāt (d. 1413 CE)","lexicon_ar":"كتاب التعريفات للشريف الجرجاني","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=23369#47981d","body_html":"<span>الصواب: خلاف الخطأ، وهما يستعملان في المجتهدات، والحق والباطل يستعملان في المعتقدات، حتى إذا سئلنا في مذهبنا ومذهب من خالفنا في الفروع، يجب علينا أن نجيب بأن مذهبنا صواب يحتمل الخطأ، ومذهب من خالفنا خطأ يحتمل الصواب، وإذا سئلنا عن معتقدنا ومعتقد من خالفنا من المعتقدات، يجب علينا أن نقول: الحق ما عليه نحن، والباطل ما عليه خصومنا. هكذا نقل عن المشايخ، وتمام المسألة في أصول الفقه.</span>"},{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_18","lexicon_en":"Al-Sharīf al-Jurjānī, Kitāb al-Taʿrīfāt (d. 1413 CE)","lexicon_ar":"كتاب التعريفات للشريف الجرجاني","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=23369#f1def3","body_html":"<span>الصواب: لغة السداد، واصطلاحًا: هو الأمر الثابت الذي لا يسوغ إنكاره، وقيل: الصواب: إصابة الحق، والفرق بين الصواب والصدق والحق؛ أن الصواب هو الأمر الثابت في نفس الأمر الذي لا يسوغ إنكاره، والصدق هو الذي يكون ما في الذهن مطابقًا لما في الخارج، والحق هو الذي يكون ما في الخارج مطابقًا لما في الذهن.</span>"}]}}